724450f-a.text:
West End Avenue, east side, from 76th to 75th Streets, showing 332 West End Avenue, "The Lombard", an early apartment house erected on the corner of 76th Street shortly before 1910. The small building in the middle of the block is an annex added around 1914 to the Hotel Willard, the old part of which adjoins "The Lombard" on 76th Street. On the N.E. Corner of 75th Street is the new apartment building erected in 1924.
About 1925
Joseph Smith, Photographer.
